line_1: Fly, fly, you rascal, for your spade and fork;
line_2: For once I'll set your lazy bones to work.

line_1: He stop'd, and leaning on his fork
The peasants urge their harvest, plie the fork
line_2: With double toil, and shiver at their work,

line_1: If I mistake not — blockhead! with a fork!
line_2: The Christian hope is — waiter, draw the cork —
